The paper deals with a problem in 3D computer vision, specifically semantic shape completion using generative modeling and latent manifold optimization. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of autoencoders and GANs for learning a distribution of embeddings also suggests that the paper may belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The optimization aspect of the algorithm suggests that it may also belong to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. The use of embeddings and the focus on generative modeling suggests that the paper may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the use of point clouds and the focus on completing incomplete shapes suggests that the paper may also belong to the natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-category.
